Hong Kong to Quarantine Ships From Japan Reactor Area for Radiation Checks

-- B y   M a r c o   L u i
-- 
2011-03-26T01:05:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-26/hong-kong-to-quarantine-ships-from-japan-reactor-area-for-radiation-checks.html
Hong Kong  will quarantine for
radiation checks ships that sailed from within 80 kilometers (50
miles) of  Japan ’s Fukushima prefecture, site of a quake-damaged
nuclear plant, the South China Morning Post reported, citing a
spokesman at the city’s Marine Department.    A quarantine zone has been established at Lamma Island,
southern Hong Kong, according to the report. Two phone calls
to the Marine Department’s information and public
relations office by Bloomberg News today were not answered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marco Lui in Hong Kong at 
 mlui11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jim McDonald at 
 jmcdonald8@bloomberg.net  